1
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:08,433
[CICADAS BUZZING ]

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,666
HMM.

3
00:00:26,333 --> 00:00:30,100
HMM, HERE'S SOMETHING I NOTICED
ABOUT JAPAN.

4
00:00:30,133 --> 00:00:35,266
EVEN THOUGH IT'S SO SMALL,
THE WEATHER VARIES SIGNIFICANTLY
FROM NORTH TO SOUTH.

5
00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:38,266
AMAIMON, I BELIEVE I TOLD YOU
THAT THE INFINITY KEY...

6
00:00:38,300 --> 00:00:41,266
WAS NOT TO BE USED
FOR SIGHTSEEING.
[GASPS ]

7
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:43,800
IS THAT THE HONEY HONEY SISTERS'
YUKATA?

8
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,533
DO YOU KNOW
HOW COLLECTIBLE THAT IS?

9
00:00:45,566 --> 00:00:48,500
EVEN IN THE HOLY LAND,
IT'S CONSIDERED
THE RAREST OF THE RARE.

10
00:00:48,533 --> 00:00:52,533
I WAS JUST STANDING IN LINE
AND WAS ABLE TO PURCHASE IT.

11
00:00:52,566 --> 00:00:54,200
WELL DONE!
YAY!

12
00:00:58,433 --> 00:01:02,400
NOW THIS IS WHAT YOU CALL
THE SOUL OF JAPAN--
ITS SAMURAI SPIRIT.

13
00:01:02,433 --> 00:01:06,200
NOT TO MENTION
THE HEART OF ITS CULTURE,
THE FABULOUS WORLD OF <i>MOE.</i>

14
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:10,066
TO HAVE A BROTHER AS AMAZING
AS YOU ARE IS TRULY A BLESSING.

15
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:11,966
THANK YOU
FOR THE COMPLIMENT.

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,400
BY THE WAY, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE I CAN FIND HIM?

17
00:01:14,433 --> 00:01:16,366
OH. HE'S OVER THERE.

18
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,733
HMM.

19
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:25,000
[AMAIMON ]
AN AMUSEMENT PARK?

20
00:01:25,033 --> 00:01:27,133
[MEPHISTO ]
THAT'S RIGHT.

21
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:35,633
[THINKING ]
YOU'RE FINALLY IN THE MOOD
TO PLAY WITH HIM.

22
00:01:35,666 --> 00:01:37,633
[CHUCKLING ]

23
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:50,500
♪ [MAN SINGING
IN JAPANESE ]

24
00:03:15,627 --> 00:03:19,227
[SHIMA ]
OH, MAN. A FIELD TRIP
TO AN AMUSEMENT PARK?

25
00:03:19,261 --> 00:03:21,302
THIS IS WHERE
YOU TAKE GIRLS ON DATES.

26
00:03:21,336 --> 00:03:22,836
THIS ISN'T
ABOUT HAVING FUN.

27
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:25,502
BY THE WAY,
HOW DID YOUR TEAM DO
ON YOUR MISSION?

28
00:03:25,536 --> 00:03:28,102
I WOULDN'T CALL IT
A MISSION.

29
00:03:28,136 --> 00:03:30,936
WOULD YOU?
A BIG-ASS SQUID'S
WHAT I'D CALL IT.

30
00:03:30,969 --> 00:03:32,502
A SQUID?

31
00:03:32,536 --> 00:03:34,702
REALLY?
REALLY.

32
00:03:34,736 --> 00:03:38,036
MAN, SITTING AROUND
THESE LOSERS IS A DRAG.
EXCUSE ME?

33
00:03:38,069 --> 00:03:42,836
HA! WE NEED PEOPLE IN CLASS
WHO CAN PULL THEIR WEIGHT,
NOT USELESS DUMBASSES LIKE THEM.

34
00:03:42,869 --> 00:03:44,869
OH.

35
00:03:46,536 --> 00:03:48,902
EASY DOES IT.
[HUFFS ]

36
00:03:48,936 --> 00:03:51,002
[SHIEMI ]
I'M SORRY I'M SO LATE.
HMM?

37
00:03:53,869 --> 00:03:55,936
HUH?

38
00:03:55,969 --> 00:03:57,436
- HUH?
- [GASPS ]

39
00:03:57,469 --> 00:04:00,569
[BOYS ]
WHOA!

40
00:04:00,602 --> 00:04:04,336
SH-SHIEMI,
WHAT'S GOING ON?
WHERE'S YOUR KIMONO?

41
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:06,769
I ASKED THE DIRECTOR
TO ISSUE ME A UNIFORM...

42
00:04:06,802 --> 00:04:09,469
BECAUSE KIMONOS AREN'T
THE BEST THING TO WEAR
ON MISSIONS.

43
00:04:09,502 --> 00:04:13,336
OH, AND ALSO BECAUSE
MISS KAMIKI WAS TEACHING ME
HOW TO WEAR IT RIGHT.

44
00:04:13,369 --> 00:04:15,869
LIKE THAT'S MY JOB?

45
00:04:15,902 --> 00:04:19,436
UM, IT DOESN'T LOOK FUNNY
ON ME, DOES IT?

46
00:04:19,469 --> 00:04:22,236
OOH, WOW,
YOU SURE LOOK CUTE,
MORIYAMA.

47
00:04:22,269 --> 00:04:23,869
MM-HMM.

48
00:04:23,902 --> 00:04:25,269
THANK YOU.

49
00:04:25,302 --> 00:04:30,136
AM I SEEING THINGS,
OR IS HER SKIRT, LIKE,
WAY, WAY TOO SHORT?

50
00:04:30,169 --> 00:04:32,969
I MEAN, DAMN!
WHY ARE YOU ASKING ME?

51
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:36,002
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
I TOTALLY SAW YOU
STARING AT HER B--

52
00:04:38,336 --> 00:04:40,036
THAT HURT, FOUR-EYES!

53
00:04:40,069 --> 00:04:43,136
OKAY, AND NOW
THAT YOU'RE ALL HERE,
LET'S GET STARTED.

54
00:04:43,169 --> 00:04:45,902
YOU'LL BE TEAMING UP
IN GROUPS OF TWO FOR TODAY.

55
00:04:45,936 --> 00:04:47,869
UH, MIWA AND TAKARA.

56
00:04:47,902 --> 00:04:49,869
YAMADA AND SUGURO.

57
00:04:49,902 --> 00:04:51,436
CRAP! THAT FIGURES.

58
00:04:51,469 --> 00:04:53,036
KAMIKI AND SHIMA.

59
00:04:53,069 --> 00:04:54,936
OKUMURA AND MORIYAMA.

60
00:04:54,969 --> 00:04:56,369
WE'RE TOGETHER, RIN.

61
00:04:56,402 --> 00:04:57,936
HUH?

62
00:04:57,969 --> 00:04:59,469
OH, SWEET.

63
00:05:03,902 --> 00:05:07,036
AS YOU MAY ALREADY KNOW,
THIS IS MEPPHYLAND.

64
00:05:07,069 --> 00:05:11,436
AND THE REASON WE'RE HERE
IS IN RESPONSE TO REPORTS
REGARDING A MISCHIEVOUS GHOST.

65
00:05:11,469 --> 00:05:14,002
TODAY, YOU ARE GOING TO BE
THE ONES TRACKING IT DOWN.

66
00:05:14,036 --> 00:05:16,802
WE'VE SEALED THE PARK OFF
FROM THE PUBLIC,

67
00:05:16,836 --> 00:05:18,902
SO YOU HAVE THE WHOLE DAY
TO FIND THE GHOST.

68
00:05:18,936 --> 00:05:22,002
ONCE YOU'VE FOUND IT,
CALL EITHER MR. TSUBAKI
OR MYSELF.

69
00:05:22,036 --> 00:05:25,369
[CLEARS THROAT ]
NOW WHAT IS THE DEFINITION
OF A GHOST?

70
00:05:25,402 --> 00:05:27,636
MISS KAMIKI?
YES, SIR.

71
00:05:27,669 --> 00:05:30,802
A GHOST IS A DEMON
THAT POSSESSES
THE VOLATILE EMISSIONS...

72
00:05:30,836 --> 00:05:33,269
FROM THE CORPSE OF EITHER
A HUMAN OR AN ANIMAL.

73
00:05:33,302 --> 00:05:36,836
IT ASSUMES AND EXPRESSES
THE EMOTIONS ITS HOST HAD
BEFORE DEATH.

74
00:05:36,869 --> 00:05:38,736
MM. VERY GOOD.

75
00:05:38,769 --> 00:05:42,102
UM, EXACTLY HOW MANY GHOSTS
ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

76
00:05:42,136 --> 00:05:44,536
THERE HAVE BEEN SIGHTINGS
ALL OVER THE PARK,

77
00:05:44,569 --> 00:05:47,502
BUT ACCORDING TO OUR INTEL,
IT'S JUST THE ONE GHOST.

78
00:05:47,536 --> 00:05:51,102
IT ALWAYS APPEARS IN THE FORM
OF A SMALL BOY, AND SO FAR,

79
00:05:51,136 --> 00:05:54,169
ITS MISCHIEF HAS BEEN LIMITED
TO ARM-PULLING AND
SKIRT-FLIPPING.

80
00:05:54,202 --> 00:05:55,702
HUH? SKIRT-FLIPPING?

81
00:05:55,736 --> 00:05:58,102
REALLY?
THAT'S CHILDISH.

82
00:05:58,136 --> 00:06:00,169
OH, WAIT.
IT IS A CHILD.

83
00:06:00,202 --> 00:06:04,102
THE PRANKS WILL ONLY GET MORE
DANGEROUS, SO IT'S IMPERATIVE
WE FIND THE GHOST QUICKLY.

84
00:06:04,136 --> 00:06:07,736
IF WE SPREAD OUT
ACROSS THE PARK,
WE'LL FIND IT IN NO TIME.

85
00:06:07,769 --> 00:06:10,102
DOES ANYONE HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS?

86
00:06:13,169 --> 00:06:15,969
ALL RIGHT.
GOOD LUCK!

87
00:06:18,643 --> 00:06:20,243
[BUZZING ]

88
00:06:26,577 --> 00:06:28,379
YOU KEEP AN EYE
ON THE RIGHT SIDE
OF THE STREET,

89
00:06:28,412 --> 00:06:30,279
AND I'LL KEEP AN EYE
ON THE LEFT, OKAY?

90
00:06:30,312 --> 00:06:31,946
SURE.

91
00:06:37,912 --> 00:06:40,012
[THINKING ]
SHE LOOKS PRETTY GOOD
IN THAT.

92
00:06:40,046 --> 00:06:42,112
THIS SORT OF
FEELS LIKE WE'RE
ON A--

93
00:06:42,146 --> 00:06:44,212
A-A DATE.

94
00:06:44,246 --> 00:06:45,612
HMM?

95
00:06:45,646 --> 00:06:49,612
[MECHANISMS GRINDING ]
[WHIMPERING ]

96
00:06:49,646 --> 00:06:51,879
UH, HEY,
ARE YOU OKAY?

97
00:06:54,679 --> 00:06:57,146
[GASPS ]
WHAT'S UP WITH THAT UGLY FACE?

98
00:06:57,179 --> 00:06:59,679
YOU SHOULD SEE YOURSELF, SHIEMI.
YOU'RE ALL PUFFED UP.

99
00:06:59,712 --> 00:07:01,946
ARE YOU MAD OR SOMETHING?
I'M NOT MAD.

100
00:07:01,979 --> 00:07:04,846
[QUAVERING ]
REALLY, I'M NOT.
I'M NOT LAUGHING EITHER.

101
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:06,112
HUH?

102
00:07:07,546 --> 00:07:10,779
[MECHANISMS GRINDING ]
WELL, HEY, WAIT UP.

103
00:07:12,146 --> 00:07:14,546
YOU'RE ACTING REALLY WEIRD.

104
00:07:24,912 --> 00:07:25,912
[GASPS ]

105
00:07:29,512 --> 00:07:31,346
[SIGHS ]

106
00:07:31,379 --> 00:07:33,379
UH, SHIEMI?

107
00:07:33,412 --> 00:07:37,912
I-I'VE ALWAYS DREAMED
THAT SOMEDAY I'D GET TO GO
TO AN AMUSEMENT PARK.

108
00:07:39,946 --> 00:07:43,879
BUT WHEN I WAS LITTLE,
I COULDN'T STAND TO BE
IN BIG CROWDS OF PEOPLE,

109
00:07:43,912 --> 00:07:46,212
SO AMUSEMENT PARKS
WERE OUT OF THE QUESTION.

110
00:07:48,212 --> 00:07:52,112
I BET THIS PLACE
CAN BE REALLY FUN
ON THE DAYS WHEN IT'S OPEN.

111
00:07:54,812 --> 00:07:57,512
MAYBE-- MAYBE NOW
I'D BE OKAY TO--

112
00:07:57,546 --> 00:08:00,412
[GROANS ]

113
00:08:00,446 --> 00:08:04,312
THEN HEY, WHY DON'T YOU AND ME
COME AND HANG OUT HERE SOMETIME?

114
00:08:07,112 --> 00:08:08,412
SURE.

115
00:08:08,446 --> 00:08:10,579
YOU REALLY WANT TO?

116
00:08:10,612 --> 00:08:12,579
[BLUBBERING ]
YOU MEAN IT?

117
00:08:12,612 --> 00:08:14,446
YOU PROMISE?
MM-HMM.

118
00:08:14,479 --> 00:08:16,646
WE'LL DEFINITELY
COME BACK.

119
00:08:16,679 --> 00:08:18,879
[LAUGHS ]
OKAY, YOU GOT IT.

120
00:08:18,912 --> 00:08:21,279
BUT FIRST WE'D BETTER FIGURE OUT
WHERE WE'RE GONNA LOOK NEXT.

121
00:08:21,312 --> 00:08:22,912
OKAY.

122
00:08:36,579 --> 00:08:39,546
[NO AUDIBLE DIALOGUE ]

123
00:08:42,812 --> 00:08:45,179
<i>[CHILD CRYING ]</i>
HUH?

124
00:08:45,212 --> 00:08:47,979
RIN?
A VOICE.

125
00:08:48,012 --> 00:08:49,846
WHAT VOICE?

126
00:08:52,479 --> 00:08:54,679
DID THAT START
ALL BY ITSELF?
SHH.

127
00:09:01,579 --> 00:09:03,646
IT'S HERE.
[GASPS ]

128
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:05,246
[MACHINERY WINDS DOWN ]

129
00:09:05,279 --> 00:09:06,712
[CRYING ]

130
00:09:10,179 --> 00:09:14,012
[BOTH GASP ]
OH, MY GOSH, RIN!
HOW'D YOU KNOW IT WAS HERE?

131
00:09:14,046 --> 00:09:17,712
UH, I JUST, YOU KNOW,
HAD A GUT FEELING.

132
00:09:17,746 --> 00:09:20,179
UM, WHY ARE YOU CRYING?

133
00:09:20,212 --> 00:09:22,779
UH, HANG ON.
I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD TALK TO IT.

134
00:09:22,812 --> 00:09:25,712
BUT LOOK AT HIM.
HE'S JUST A LITTLE KID.

135
00:09:25,746 --> 00:09:28,412
HE CAN'T REALLY BE
THAT DANGEROUS, CAN HE?

136
00:09:28,446 --> 00:09:30,512
[CRYING ]

137
00:09:30,546 --> 00:09:31,912
HEY, YOU!
[SHRIEKS ]

138
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:33,612
CUT OUT THE LAME-ASS CRYING
ALREADY.

139
00:09:33,646 --> 00:09:35,079
[SCREAMS ]

140
00:09:35,112 --> 00:09:37,446
OH, COME ON.
YOU DON'T HAVE
TO YELL AT HIM.

141
00:09:37,479 --> 00:09:40,412
YEAH,
BUT I WAS JUST--
[GASPS ]

142
00:09:40,446 --> 00:09:43,179
I WAS ALWAYS
SO VERY SICK...

143
00:09:43,212 --> 00:09:47,646
AND-- AND MY DADDY AND MOMMY
PROMISED ME THEY'D TAKE ME HERE
WHEN I GOT BETTER.

144
00:09:47,679 --> 00:09:50,212
ALL I WANTED
WAS TO COME HERE AND PLAY.

145
00:09:50,246 --> 00:09:56,079
BUT NOW THAT I'M DEAD,
I CAN'T PLAY WITH ANYONE.

146
00:09:56,112 --> 00:09:59,079
I'M SORRY. THAT MUST BE
PRETTY HARD FOR YOU.

147
00:09:59,112 --> 00:10:01,379
[CRYING ]

148
00:10:01,412 --> 00:10:02,912
SHUT UP, OLD BAG!

149
00:10:04,646 --> 00:10:07,612
- HUH?
- [LAUGHS ]
YOU DUMMIES!

150
00:10:10,746 --> 00:10:12,746
THAT ROTTEN,
SLIMY LITTLE PIECE OF--

151
00:10:12,779 --> 00:10:14,679
I'VE BEEN WANTING
TO DO THAT FOR--

152
00:10:14,712 --> 00:10:17,312
- COME BACK HERE, DAMN IT!
- WAIT, RIN.

153
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:20,946
[LAUGHING ]
BUTT-HEAD!

154
00:10:23,012 --> 00:10:24,279
LITTLE BRAT!

155
00:10:27,246 --> 00:10:29,012
WAIT UP!

156
00:10:31,612 --> 00:10:33,246
[BOTH PANTING ]

157
00:10:41,746 --> 00:10:44,146
LITTLE PERVERT.
WHERE IS HE?

158
00:10:45,512 --> 00:10:48,479
RIN, I'M GONNA GO LOOK
OVER THERE, OKAY?

159
00:10:48,512 --> 00:10:50,746
SURE.

160
00:10:59,512 --> 00:11:01,046
GOTCHA!

161
00:11:05,379 --> 00:11:06,846
[GASPS ]

162
00:11:10,512 --> 00:11:12,179
[SIGHS ]

163
00:11:14,279 --> 00:11:15,846
WOW.

164
00:11:17,846 --> 00:11:19,479
[LAUGHING ]

165
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:22,779
YOU BIG DUMMY!
HEY, COME HERE!

166
00:11:25,012 --> 00:11:27,812
TRY AND CATCH ME
IF YOU CAN.
[LAUGHS ]

167
00:11:27,846 --> 00:11:29,846
OWIE.

168
00:11:29,879 --> 00:11:33,112
THAT LITTLE--
WHY IS HE BEHAVING LIKE THAT?

169
00:11:35,312 --> 00:11:38,512
[RIN]THAT'S RIGHT.
WE'RE SUPPOSED TO CALL IN
WHEN WE'VE FOUND THE GHOST.

170
00:11:38,546 --> 00:11:40,579
[BEEPING ]

171
00:11:40,612 --> 00:11:42,412
[LINE RINGING ]
HMM.

172
00:11:42,446 --> 00:11:44,179
[GASPS ]

173
00:11:44,212 --> 00:11:46,579
WHO ARE YOU
SUPPOSED TO BE?
GIVE THAT BACK!

174
00:11:49,579 --> 00:11:51,779
WHO AM I?
OH, RIGHT.

175
00:11:51,812 --> 00:11:54,979
MY NAME IS AMAIMON.
I'M A DEMON KING.

176
00:11:55,012 --> 00:11:57,346
YOU COULD SAY
I'M AN OLDER BROTHER OF YOURS.

177
00:11:57,379 --> 00:11:58,912
NICE TO MEET YA.

178
00:11:58,946 --> 00:12:01,112
OH, AND I'M NOT GIVING
THIS BACK.

179
00:12:01,146 --> 00:12:03,612
YOU'RE A DEMON?

180
00:12:03,646 --> 00:12:06,212
AHA. THIS IS THE KOMA SWORD.

181
00:12:06,246 --> 00:12:07,912
HEY! GIVE IT BACK!

182
00:12:07,946 --> 00:12:11,112
NEAT. LET'S TAKE IT OUT
FOR A SPIN AND SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

183
00:12:13,879 --> 00:12:15,746
NO!

184
00:12:28,501 --> 00:12:30,201
[CICADAS BUZZING ]

185
00:12:33,168 --> 00:12:34,768
[GROANS ]

186
00:12:34,801 --> 00:12:38,001
[ELECTRONIC SCREECHING ]
[GROANS ]

187
00:12:40,423 --> 00:12:43,056
WOULD IT KILL YOU TO ACTUALLY
HELP ME LOOK FOR A CHANGE?

188
00:12:43,090 --> 00:12:45,290
[ELECTRONIC EXPLOSION ]

189
00:12:45,323 --> 00:12:46,890
[GASPS ]

190
00:12:51,423 --> 00:12:52,723
HEY!

191
00:12:52,756 --> 00:12:56,390
[YAWNING ]

192
00:12:56,423 --> 00:12:59,123
FOUND YOU!

193
00:12:59,156 --> 00:13:01,756
[LAUGHS ]
YOU'RE SO LAME!

194
00:13:01,790 --> 00:13:05,190
UH, THIS TIME I SWEAR
I'M GONNA CATCH YOU.

195
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:09,723
- I-I WANNA GET OFF NOW.
- [LAUGHS ]

196
00:13:09,756 --> 00:13:12,190
[SHIEMI SCREAMING ]

197
00:13:20,556 --> 00:13:22,023
[RIN ]
CUT IT OUT!

198
00:13:31,090 --> 00:13:33,290
- DON'T MESS WITH THAT.
- I GET IT.

199
00:13:33,323 --> 00:13:37,090
THE BLADE OF THE SWORD ACTS
LIKE A SMALL ENTRANCE
LEADING TO GEHENNA.

200
00:13:37,123 --> 00:13:39,956
AND THE SCABBARD HERE
ACTS AS KIND OF A DOORWAY TO IT.

201
00:13:39,990 --> 00:13:43,090
IF I SHEATH THE BLADE,
THE ENTRANCE IS CLOSED.

202
00:13:43,123 --> 00:13:45,123
WHEN I DRAW IT OUT,
IT'S OPENED.

203
00:13:45,156 --> 00:13:47,790
DAMN IT, WOULD YOU
MAKE UP YOUR MIND?

204
00:13:47,823 --> 00:13:50,590
HMM, ALL RIGHT.
I'LL KEEP IT OPEN.

205
00:13:50,623 --> 00:13:52,456
[GRUNTS ]

206
00:13:52,490 --> 00:13:57,123
HUH. SO YOUR FLAMES
AND YOUR POWER LIE IN GEHENNA...

207
00:13:57,156 --> 00:13:59,290
WHILE YOUR BODY
IS HERE IN ASSIAH.

208
00:13:59,323 --> 00:14:01,356
YEAH, WHATEVER.

209
00:14:05,990 --> 00:14:08,423
UH-OH, YOU BROKE
MY BROTHER'S HEAD.

210
00:14:08,456 --> 00:14:10,656
JUST TELL ME
WHAT THE HELL
YOU'RE AFTER, DAMN IT.

211
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:14,656
OH, NOTHING. I WAS BORED,
SO I JUST CAME OVER TO PLAY.

212
00:14:14,690 --> 00:14:15,923
HUH?

213
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:20,390
SINCE WE'RE HANGING OUT
AT THE AMUSEMENT PARK,

214
00:14:20,423 --> 00:14:22,956
WE SHOULD AMUSE OURSELVES
AS MUCH AS POSSIBLE.

215
00:14:22,990 --> 00:14:24,590
[SNAPS FINGER ]

216
00:14:29,390 --> 00:14:30,956
[GASPS ]

217
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:36,123
♪ [CALLIOPE ]

218
00:14:36,156 --> 00:14:39,656
♪ [CIRCUS MUSIC ]

219
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:41,490
HUH?
WHAT THE--

220
00:14:41,523 --> 00:14:43,423
- HUH?
- [GASPS ]

221
00:14:43,456 --> 00:14:45,223
[CELL PHONE RINGS ]

222
00:14:45,256 --> 00:14:47,956
[TSUBAKI ]
OKUMURA, DID YOU SWITCH
THE POWER ON JUST NOW?

223
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:50,556
NO. IT WASN'T ME.
LOOK AROUND.

224
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:53,223
IS THERE ANYTHING STRANGE
HAPPENING ANYWHERE NEAR YOU?

225
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:57,990
THIS GUY'S GOT SOME STYLE.

226
00:14:58,023 --> 00:15:00,823
I'VE STUDIED
ALL YOUR JAPANESE GAMES TOO.

227
00:15:00,856 --> 00:15:03,123
♪ HEY, DEMON, OVER HERE ♪

228
00:15:03,156 --> 00:15:05,223
♪ FOLLOW THE SOUND
OF CLAPPING ♪

229
00:15:05,256 --> 00:15:06,923
SON OF A--

230
00:15:06,956 --> 00:15:08,890
DON'T TEASE ME,
YOU BASTARD!

231
00:15:10,790 --> 00:15:13,323
[GHOST ]
HEY, DUMMY.
WAKE UP.

232
00:15:13,356 --> 00:15:14,456
[GASPS ]

233
00:15:15,423 --> 00:15:17,290
O-ONE SECOND.

234
00:15:17,323 --> 00:15:18,890
[LAUGHING ]

235
00:15:18,923 --> 00:15:21,423
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE TO HEAR.

236
00:15:21,456 --> 00:15:24,190
♪ HEY, DEMON, OVER HERE ♪
HEY, WAIT!

237
00:15:26,223 --> 00:15:27,790
[THINKING ]
I WONDER IF HE'S--

238
00:15:27,823 --> 00:15:30,723
I WAS ALWAYS SO VERY SICK, AND--

239
00:15:30,756 --> 00:15:34,723
I-I'VE ALWAYS DREAMED
THAT SOMEDAY I'D GET TO GO
TO AN AMUSEMENT PARK.

240
00:15:34,756 --> 00:15:36,223
[LAUGHING ]

241
00:15:36,256 --> 00:15:38,890
THAT LITTLE GHOST
IS JUST LIKE ME.

242
00:15:38,923 --> 00:15:41,590
IF THAT'S THE CASE--

243
00:15:41,623 --> 00:15:46,490
OKAY! IF THAT'S HOW
YOU WANNA PLAY, COME BACK HERE!

244
00:15:46,523 --> 00:15:48,823
COME BACK HERE!

245
00:15:48,856 --> 00:15:52,590
SO THE OTHER DAY
I HAD SOME FREE TIME,
AND I WENT TO THE BEACH.

246
00:15:52,623 --> 00:15:54,190
[GRUNTING ]

247
00:15:54,223 --> 00:15:56,223
[THINKING ]
WHAT THE HELL'S
HE TALKING ABOUT?

248
00:16:10,123 --> 00:16:12,890
LOOK AT ME!
SURFING IS SO AWESOME!

249
00:16:12,923 --> 00:16:14,956
COME ON, YOU BASTARD!

250
00:16:18,056 --> 00:16:20,490
- WHAT THE--
- HERE'S ANOTHER GAME
I LEARNED TO PLAY.

251
00:16:25,923 --> 00:16:29,656
WHAT WAS THAT?
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON
OVER THERE?

252
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:31,590
WHOA!

253
00:16:31,623 --> 00:16:34,790
THERE'S NO WAY A GHOST COULD
HAVE CAUSED THAT TO HAPPEN.

254
00:16:34,823 --> 00:16:37,223
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
AT WORK OVER THERE.

255
00:16:41,856 --> 00:16:44,623
[GRUNTING ]

256
00:16:44,656 --> 00:16:46,323
I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT.

257
00:16:46,356 --> 00:16:49,656
WHY WOULD FATHER
AND MY BIG BROTHER
BE SO OBSESSED WITH THIS ONE?

258
00:16:51,956 --> 00:16:54,590
[RIN GRUNTING ]

259
00:16:54,623 --> 00:16:57,423
[GROANING ]

260
00:17:02,590 --> 00:17:03,856
YAY!
[LAUGHS ]

261
00:17:03,890 --> 00:17:06,923
I'M UP HERE!

262
00:17:08,123 --> 00:17:11,023
[BLOWS LANDING ]
[RIN GRUNTING ]

263
00:17:11,778 --> 00:17:13,700
THIS IS SO DISAPPOINTING.

264
00:17:13,734 --> 00:17:16,667
HERE I WAS HOPING
YOU'D HELP ME KILL MY BOREDOM.

265
00:17:23,900 --> 00:17:25,967
[SHOUTING ]

266
00:17:29,534 --> 00:17:31,267
YAY!

267
00:17:35,967 --> 00:17:38,434
[SHOUTING ]

268
00:17:38,467 --> 00:17:41,567
YES! HOORAY!
THAT'S THE SPIRIT!

269
00:17:44,834 --> 00:17:46,634
[METALLIC GROANING ]

270
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,500
[GASPING ]
EARTHQUAKE.

271
00:17:57,934 --> 00:17:59,634
[ROARING ]

272
00:17:59,667 --> 00:18:00,900
[HISSING ]

273
00:18:03,034 --> 00:18:04,667
[AIR HISSING ]

274
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:07,267
[GASPS ]
WHAT'S GOING ON?
[LAUGHS ]

275
00:18:09,267 --> 00:18:11,100
[GULPS ]
[LAUGHS ]

276
00:18:11,134 --> 00:18:13,334
COOL! IT'S JUST LIKE A MOVIE!

277
00:18:13,367 --> 00:18:15,200
COME ON.
WE'RE DONE PLAYING TAG NOW.

278
00:18:15,234 --> 00:18:17,600
[GHOST CONTINUES LAUGHING ]

279
00:18:17,634 --> 00:18:20,300
- [CREAKING, BANGS ]
- [GASPS ]

280
00:18:20,334 --> 00:18:22,667
[SHIEMI SCREAMING ]
[GASPS ]

281
00:18:24,867 --> 00:18:27,834
SOMEONE HELP!
NEE!

282
00:18:27,867 --> 00:18:28,967
[THINKING ]
SHIEMI!

283
00:18:35,267 --> 00:18:37,667
RUN, DUMMY!
RUN!

284
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:42,300
<i>I WON'T MAKE IT.</i>
[ROARS ]

285
00:18:50,700 --> 00:18:53,400
NEE!
[LAUGHS ]

286
00:18:53,434 --> 00:18:55,900
AWESOME!
STOP LAUGHING.

287
00:18:55,934 --> 00:18:57,467
IT'S NOT FUNNY.
WE ALMOST DIED.

288
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,900
BUT I'M ALREADY DEAD.

289
00:18:59,934 --> 00:19:01,900
OH, RIGHT.

290
00:19:01,934 --> 00:19:04,400
I WAS ALWAYS SICK,
SO I NEVER GOT TO PLAY OUTSIDE.

291
00:19:04,434 --> 00:19:09,467
I NEVER GOT IN TROUBLE,
AND NOBODY EVER CUDDLED ME.
NOT UNTIL TODAY ANYWAY.

292
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:13,400
[LAUGHS ]
I HAD THE BEST TIME EVER
PLAYING WITH YOU.

293
00:19:13,434 --> 00:19:15,700
OH.

294
00:19:15,734 --> 00:19:17,900
THANKS FOR TODAY, BIG SIS.
IT WAS FUN.

295
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:25,767
[PANTING ]

296
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,134
[GRUNTS ]

297
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:29,934
IS THAT IT?
ARE YOU DONE WITH YOUR SHOW?

298
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:32,300
HOW BORING FOR ME.

299
00:19:32,334 --> 00:19:37,800
MY BROTHER DIDN'T WANT ME
TO DO THIS, BUT THE FUN'S OVER,
SO I GUESS I CAN BREAK THIS NOW.

300
00:19:37,834 --> 00:19:40,434
NO! CUT IT OUT.

301
00:19:40,467 --> 00:19:42,934
DEVOUR THE EIGHT PRINCESSES.

302
00:19:47,067 --> 00:19:48,300
HMM?

303
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,567
SLAY THE SERPENT!

304
00:19:53,534 --> 00:19:55,834
OOH, AND WHO
MIGHT YOU BE?

305
00:19:55,867 --> 00:19:59,667
YOU'RE AMAIMON,
KING OF EARTH, AREN'T YOU?

306
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:04,234
I WONDER HOW A BIG SHOT DEMON
LIKE YOU GOT INTO THE ACADEMY.

307
00:20:04,267 --> 00:20:05,900
WHAT, DID MEPHISTO SUMMON YOU?

308
00:20:05,934 --> 00:20:07,534
I WISH YOU'D GET OUT OF MY WAY.

309
00:20:07,567 --> 00:20:10,400
I WISH YOU'D
GET OUT OF MY WAY.

310
00:20:10,434 --> 00:20:12,800
HMM.

311
00:20:12,834 --> 00:20:14,434
[PANTING ]

312
00:20:20,300 --> 00:20:22,300
OH, WELL.
I CHANGED MY MIND.

313
00:20:23,767 --> 00:20:25,167
PERHAPS ANOTHER TIME.

314
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:28,067
HEY, GET BACK HERE!
FAREWELL!

315
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:29,600
[RIN GROANING ]

316
00:20:29,634 --> 00:20:32,800
THE OTHERS
WILL BE HERE SOON.
HIDE THE TAIL, WILL YA?

317
00:20:39,134 --> 00:20:43,000
[THINKING ]
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HE TOOK MY SWORD SO EASY.

318
00:20:43,034 --> 00:20:45,434
I CAN'T BELIEVE
HOW STRONG HE WAS.

319
00:20:45,467 --> 00:20:49,467
AND FOR A SECOND THERE,
I LOST CONTROL.

320
00:20:52,067 --> 00:20:55,034
I HAVEN'T CHANGED ONE BIT.

321
00:20:55,067 --> 00:20:56,767
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

322
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,000
RIN! ARE YOU OKAY?

323
00:20:59,034 --> 00:21:01,900
- DON'T TOUCH ME!
- [GASPS ]

324
00:21:01,934 --> 00:21:04,700
BUT, RIN--

325
00:21:04,734 --> 00:21:07,000
SORRY.
I-I'M OKAY.

326
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:12,467
SO, ANYWAY, HOW WERE THINGS
ON YOUR END OF THE PARK?

327
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,700
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THAT LITTLE BRAT?

328
00:21:14,734 --> 00:21:16,534
HE JUST DISAPPEARED.

329
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:18,767
HE CALLED ME BIG SIS
AND SAID THANKS.

330
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,634
OH. GOOD.

331
00:21:21,834 --> 00:21:26,267
RIN, WE SHOULD DEFINITELY
COME BACK HERE SOMEDAY.

332
00:21:27,367 --> 00:21:29,467
YEAH. YOU GOT IT.

333
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,500
[YUKIO ]
SHIEMI!

334
00:21:31,534 --> 00:21:33,167
YUKI.

335
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:35,034
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

336
00:21:35,067 --> 00:21:37,034
I AM, BUT I THINK
RIN GOT HURT,

337
00:21:37,067 --> 00:21:38,967
AND HE'S GOING TO NEED
SOME TREATMENT.

338
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,467
RIN, ARE YOU--
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

339
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:44,867
SERIOUSLY, YUKIO,
IT WAS TAKING YOU FOREVER
TO GET HERE,

340
00:21:44,900 --> 00:21:47,000
SO I HAD TO MAKE A MOVE.

341
00:21:48,334 --> 00:21:50,034
BEEN A LONG TIME, HASN'T IT?

342
00:21:50,067 --> 00:21:54,567
IT CAN'T BE.
YUKIO, WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON AROUND HERE?

343
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:57,500
I CAN'T GO ANOTHER DAY
IN THIS DAMN HOODIE ANYWAY.

344
00:22:04,667 --> 00:22:06,134
HUH?
POP!

345
00:22:06,167 --> 00:22:08,834
SORRY, KID.
I'M NOT YOUR CLASSMATE.

346
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:11,467
I'M AN INSPECTOR
WITH THE KNIGHTS
OF THE TRUE CROSS.

347
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:13,734
VATICAN H.Q. SENT ME
TO INVESTIGATE...

348
00:22:13,767 --> 00:22:15,900
A DANGEROUS ELEMENT
IN THE JAPAN BRANCH.

349
00:22:15,934 --> 00:22:20,600
I'M SENIOR EXORCIST FIRST CLASS
SHURA KIRIGAKURE.

350
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,234
[ALL STAMMERING ]

351
00:22:27,934 --> 00:22:29,400
[CHUCKLES ]

352
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:37,700
♪ [MAN SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

353
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:06,367
[SHURA]WHY'D YOU HIDE
THE EXISTENCE OF THE SON
OF SATAN FROM THE ORDER?

354
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,334
[MEPHISTO ]
I DIDN'T HIDE ANYTHING
FROM ANYONE.

355
00:24:08,367 --> 00:24:12,000
YES, I TOOK HIM IN, BUT IT WAS
ALL FOR THE SAKE OF THE ORDER
AND ITS FUTURE.

356
00:24:12,034 --> 00:24:15,867
[SHURA ]
I REALLY WANTED
TO BELIEVE THAT... SHIRO.

